100struct intel_dvo {
101 struct intel_encoder base;
102
103 struct intel_dvo_device dev;
104
105 struct intel_connector *attached_connector;
106
107 bool panel_wants_dither;
108};
109
110static struct intel_dvo *enc_to_dvo(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
111{
112 return container_of(encoder, struct intel_dvo, base);
113}
114
115static struct intel_dvo *intel_attached_dvo(struct drm_connector *connector)
116{
117 return enc_to_dvo(intel_attached_encoder(connector));
118}
119
120static bool intel_dvo_connector_get_hw_state(struct intel_connector *connector)
121{
122 struct drm_device *dev = connector->base.dev;
123 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
124 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo = intel_attached_dvo(&connector->base);
125 u32 tmp;
126
127 tmp = I915_READ(intel_dvo->dev.dvo_reg);
128
129 if (!(tmp & DVO_ENABLE))
130 return false;
131
132 return intel_dvo->dev.dev_ops->get_hw_state(&intel_dvo->dev);
133}
134
135static bool intel_dvo_get_hw_state(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
136 enum i915_pipe *pipe)
137{
138 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
139 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
140 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo = enc_to_dvo(encoder);
141 u32 tmp;
142
143 tmp = I915_READ(intel_dvo->dev.dvo_reg);
144
145 if (!(tmp & DVO_ENABLE))
146 return false;
147
148 *pipe = PORT_TO_PIPE(tmp);
149
150 return true;
151}
152
153static void intel_dvo_get_config(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
154 struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
155{
156 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = encoder->base.dev->dev_private;
157 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo = enc_to_dvo(encoder);
158 u32 tmp, flags = 0;
159
160 tmp = I915_READ(intel_dvo->dev.dvo_reg);
161 if (tmp & DVO_HSYNC_ACTIVE_HIGH)
162 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC;
163 else
164 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC;
165 if (tmp & DVO_VSYNC_ACTIVE_HIGH)
166 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC;
167 else
168 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC;
169
170 pipe_config->base.adjusted_mode.flags |= flags;
171
172 pipe_config->base.adjusted_mode.crtc_clock = pipe_config->port_clock;
173}
174
175static void intel_disable_dvo(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
176{
177 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = encoder->base.dev->dev_private;
178 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo = enc_to_dvo(encoder);
179 u32 dvo_reg = intel_dvo->dev.dvo_reg;
180 u32 temp = I915_READ(dvo_reg);
181
182 intel_dvo->dev.dev_ops->dpms(&intel_dvo->dev, false);
183 I915_WRITE(dvo_reg, temp & ~DVO_ENABLE);
184 I915_READ(dvo_reg);
185}
186
187static void intel_enable_dvo(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
188{
189 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = encoder->base.dev->dev_private;
190 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo = enc_to_dvo(encoder);
191 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
192 u32 dvo_reg = intel_dvo->dev.dvo_reg;
193 u32 temp = I915_READ(dvo_reg);
194
195 intel_dvo->dev.dev_ops->mode_set(&intel_dvo->dev,
196 &crtc->config->base.mode,
197 &crtc->config->base.adjusted_mode);
198
199 I915_WRITE(dvo_reg, temp | DVO_ENABLE);
200 I915_READ(dvo_reg);
201
202 intel_dvo->dev.dev_ops->dpms(&intel_dvo->dev, true);
203}
204
205static enum drm_mode_status
206intel_dvo_mode_valid(struct drm_connector *connector,
207 struct drm_display_mode *mode)
208{
209 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo = intel_attached_dvo(connector);
210 const struct drm_display_mode *fixed_mode =
211 to_intel_connector(connector)->panel.fixed_mode;
212 int max_dotclk = to_i915(connector->dev)->max_dotclk_freq;
213 int target_clock = mode->clock;
214
215 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_DBLSCAN)
216 return MODE_NO_DBLESCAN;
217
218 /* XXX: Validate clock range */
219
220 if (fixed_mode) {
221 if (mode->hdisplay > fixed_mode->hdisplay)
222 return MODE_PANEL;
223 if (mode->vdisplay > fixed_mode->vdisplay)
224 return MODE_PANEL;
225
226 target_clock = fixed_mode->clock;
227 }
228
229 if (target_clock > max_dotclk)
230 return MODE_CLOCK_HIGH;
231
232 return intel_dvo->dev.dev_ops->mode_valid(&intel_dvo->dev, mode);
233}
234
235static bool intel_dvo_compute_config(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
236 struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
237{
238 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo = enc_to_dvo(encoder);
239 const struct drm_display_mode *fixed_mode =
240 intel_dvo->attached_connector->panel.fixed_mode;
241 struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode = &pipe_config->base.adjusted_mode;
242
243 /* If we have timings from the BIOS for the panel, put them in
244 * to the adjusted mode. The CRTC will be set up for this mode,
245 * with the panel scaling set up to source from the H/VDisplay
246 * of the original mode.
247 */
248 if (fixed_mode)
249 intel_fixed_panel_mode(fixed_mode, adjusted_mode);
250
251 return true;
252}
253
254static void intel_dvo_pre_enable(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
255{
256 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
257 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
258 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
259 const struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode = &crtc->config->base.adjusted_mode;
260 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo = enc_to_dvo(encoder);
261 int pipe = crtc->pipe;
262 u32 dvo_val;
263 u32 dvo_reg = intel_dvo->dev.dvo_reg, dvo_srcdim_reg;
264
265 switch (dvo_reg) {
266 case DVOA:
267 default:
268 dvo_srcdim_reg = DVOA_SRCDIM;
269 break;
270 case DVOB:
271 dvo_srcdim_reg = DVOB_SRCDIM;
272 break;
273 case DVOC:
274 dvo_srcdim_reg = DVOC_SRCDIM;
275 break;
276 }
277
278 /* Save the data order, since I don't know what it should be set to. */
279 dvo_val = I915_READ(dvo_reg) &
280 (DVO_PRESERVE_MASK | DVO_DATA_ORDER_GBRG);
281 dvo_val |= DVO_DATA_ORDER_FP | DVO_BORDER_ENABLE |
282 DVO_BLANK_ACTIVE_HIGH;
283
284 if (pipe == 1)
285 dvo_val |= DVO_PIPE_B_SELECT;
286 dvo_val |= DVO_PIPE_STALL;
287 if (adjusted_mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC)
288 dvo_val |= DVO_HSYNC_ACTIVE_HIGH;
289 if (adjusted_mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC)
290 dvo_val |= DVO_VSYNC_ACTIVE_HIGH;
291
292 /*I915_WRITE(DVOB_SRCDIM,
293 (adjusted_mode->crtc_hdisplay << DVO_SRCDIM_HORIZONTAL_SHIFT) |
294 (adjusted_mode->crtc_vdisplay << DVO_SRCDIM_VERTICAL_SHIFT));*/
295 I915_WRITE(dvo_srcdim_reg,
296 (adjusted_mode->crtc_hdisplay << DVO_SRCDIM_HORIZONTAL_SHIFT) |
297 (adjusted_mode->crtc_vdisplay << DVO_SRCDIM_VERTICAL_SHIFT));
298 /*I915_WRITE(DVOB, dvo_val);*/
299 I915_WRITE(dvo_reg, dvo_val);
300}

302/**
303 * Detect the output connection on our DVO device.
304 *
305 * Unimplemented.
306 */
307static enum drm_connector_status
308intel_dvo_detect(struct drm_connector *connector, bool force)
309{
310 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo = intel_attached_dvo(connector);
311 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("[CONNECTOR:%d:%s]\n",
312 connector->base.id, connector->name);
313 return intel_dvo->dev.dev_ops->detect(&intel_dvo->dev);
314}
315
316static int intel_dvo_get_modes(struct drm_connector *connector)
317{
318 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = connector->dev->dev_private;
319 const struct drm_display_mode *fixed_mode =
320 to_intel_connector(connector)->panel.fixed_mode;
321
322 /* We should probably have an i2c driver get_modes function for those
323 * devices which will have a fixed set of modes determined by the chip
324 * (TV-out, for example), but for now with just TMDS and LVDS,
325 * that's not the case.
326 */
327 intel_ddc_get_modes(connector,
328 intel_gmbus_get_adapter(dev_priv, GMBUS_PIN_DPC));
329 if (!list_empty(&connector->probed_modes))
330 return 1;
331
332 if (fixed_mode) {
333 struct drm_display_mode *mode;
334 mode = drm_mode_duplicate(connector->dev, fixed_mode);
335 if (mode) {
336 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, mode);
337 return 1;
338 }
339 }
340
341 return 0;
342}
343
344static void intel_dvo_destroy(struct drm_connector *connector)
345{
346 drm_connector_cleanup(connector);
347 intel_panel_fini(&to_intel_connector(connector)->panel);
348 kfree(connector);
349}

367static void intel_dvo_enc_destroy(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
368{
369 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo = enc_to_dvo(to_intel_encoder(encoder));
370
371 if (intel_dvo->dev.dev_ops->destroy)
372 intel_dvo->dev.dev_ops->destroy(&intel_dvo->dev);
373
374 intel_encoder_destroy(encoder);
375}

377static const struct drm_encoder_funcs intel_dvo_enc_funcs = {
378 .destroy = intel_dvo_enc_destroy,
379};

381/**
382 * Attempts to get a fixed panel timing for LVDS (currently only the i830).
383 *
384 * Other chips with DVO LVDS will need to extend this to deal with the LVDS
385 * chip being on DVOB/C and having multiple pipes.
386 */
387static struct drm_display_mode *
388intel_dvo_get_current_mode(struct drm_connector *connector)
389{
390 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
391 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
392 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo = intel_attached_dvo(connector);
393 uint32_t dvo_val = I915_READ(intel_dvo->dev.dvo_reg);
394 struct drm_display_mode *mode = NULL;
395
396 /* If the DVO port is active, that'll be the LVDS, so we can pull out
397 * its timings to get how the BIOS set up the panel.
398 */
399 if (dvo_val & DVO_ENABLE) {
400 struct drm_crtc *crtc;
401 int pipe = (dvo_val & DVO_PIPE_B_SELECT) ? 1 : 0;
402
403 crtc = intel_get_crtc_for_pipe(dev, pipe);
404 if (crtc) {
405 mode = intel_crtc_mode_get(dev, crtc);
406 if (mode) {
407 mode->type |= DRM_MODE_TYPE_PREFERRED;
408 if (dvo_val & DVO_HSYNC_ACTIVE_HIGH)
409 mode->flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC;
410 if (dvo_val & DVO_VSYNC_ACTIVE_HIGH)
411 mode->flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC;
412 }
413 }
414 }
415
416 return mode;
417}
418
419void intel_dvo_init(struct drm_device *dev)
420{
421 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
422 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder;
423 struct intel_dvo *intel_dvo;
424 struct intel_connector *intel_connector;
425 int i;
426 int encoder_type = DRM_MODE_ENCODER_NONE;
427
428 intel_dvo = kzalloc(sizeof(*intel_dvo), GFP_KERNEL);
429 if (!intel_dvo)
430 return;
431
432 intel_connector = intel_connector_alloc();
433 if (!intel_connector) {
434 kfree(intel_dvo);
435 return;
436 }
437
438 intel_dvo->attached_connector = intel_connector;
439
440 intel_encoder = &intel_dvo->base;
441 drm_encoder_init(dev, &intel_encoder->base,
442 &intel_dvo_enc_funcs, encoder_type);
443
444 intel_encoder->disable = intel_disable_dvo;
445 intel_encoder->enable = intel_enable_dvo;
446 intel_encoder->get_hw_state = intel_dvo_get_hw_state;
447 intel_encoder->get_config = intel_dvo_get_config;
448 intel_encoder->compute_config = intel_dvo_compute_config;
449 intel_encoder->pre_enable = intel_dvo_pre_enable;
450 intel_connector->get_hw_state = intel_dvo_connector_get_hw_state;
451 intel_connector->unregister = intel_connector_unregister;
452
453 /* Now, try to find a controller */
454 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(intel_dvo_devices); i++) {
455 struct drm_connector *connector = &intel_connector->base;
456 const struct intel_dvo_device *dvo = &intel_dvo_devices[i];
457 struct i2c_adapter *i2c;
458 int gpio;
459 bool dvoinit;
460 enum i915_pipe pipe;
461 uint32_t dpll[I915_MAX_PIPES];
462
463 /* Allow the I2C driver info to specify the GPIO to be used in
464 * special cases, but otherwise default to what's defined
465 * in the spec.
466 */
467 if (intel_gmbus_is_valid_pin(dev_priv, dvo->gpio))
468 gpio = dvo->gpio;
469 else if (dvo->type == INTEL_DVO_CHIP_LVDS)
470 gpio = GMBUS_PIN_SSC;
471 else
472 gpio = GMBUS_PIN_DPB;
473
474 /* Set up the I2C bus necessary for the chip we're probing.
475 * It appears that everything is on GPIOE except for panels
476 * on i830 laptops, which are on GPIOB (DVOA).
477 */
478 i2c = intel_gmbus_get_adapter(dev_priv, gpio);
479
480 intel_dvo->dev = *dvo;
481
482 /* GMBUS NAK handling seems to be unstable, hence let the
483 * transmitter detection run in bit banging mode for now.
484 */
485 intel_gmbus_force_bit(i2c, true);
486
487 /* ns2501 requires the DVO 2x clock before it will
488 * respond to i2c accesses, so make sure we have
489 * have the clock enabled before we attempt to
490 * initialize the device.
491 */
492 for_each_pipe(dev_priv, pipe) {
493 dpll[pipe] = I915_READ(DPLL(pipe));
494 I915_WRITE(DPLL(pipe), dpll[pipe] | DPLL_DVO_2X_MODE);
495 }
496
497 dvoinit = dvo->dev_ops->init(&intel_dvo->dev, i2c);
498
499 /* restore the DVO 2x clock state to original */
500 for_each_pipe(dev_priv, pipe) {
501 I915_WRITE(DPLL(pipe), dpll[pipe]);
502 }
503
504 intel_gmbus_force_bit(i2c, false);
505
506 if (!dvoinit)
507 continue;
508
509 intel_encoder->type = INTEL_OUTPUT_DVO;
510 intel_encoder->crtc_mask = (1 << 0) | (1 << 1);
511 switch (dvo->type) {
512 case INTEL_DVO_CHIP_TMDS:
513 intel_encoder->cloneable = (1 << INTEL_OUTPUT_ANALOG) |
514 (1 << INTEL_OUTPUT_DVO);
515 drm_connector_init(dev, connector,
516 &intel_dvo_connector_funcs,
517 DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_DVII);
518 encoder_type = DRM_MODE_ENCODER_TMDS;
519 break;
520 case INTEL_DVO_CHIP_LVDS:
521 intel_encoder->cloneable = 0;
522 drm_connector_init(dev, connector,
523 &intel_dvo_connector_funcs,
524 DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_LVDS);
525 encoder_type = DRM_MODE_ENCODER_LVDS;
526 break;
527 }
528
529 drm_connector_helper_add(connector,
530 &intel_dvo_connector_helper_funcs);
531 connector->display_info.subpixel_order = SubPixelHorizontalRGB;
532 connector->interlace_allowed = false;
533 connector->doublescan_allowed = false;
534
535 intel_connector_attach_encoder(intel_connector, intel_encoder);
536 if (dvo->type == INTEL_DVO_CHIP_LVDS) {
537 /* For our LVDS chipsets, we should hopefully be able
538 * to dig the fixed panel mode out of the BIOS data.
539 * However, it's in a different format from the BIOS
540 * data on chipsets with integrated LVDS (stored in AIM
541 * headers, likely), so for now, just get the current
542 * mode being output through DVO.
543 */
544 intel_panel_init(&intel_connector->panel,
545 intel_dvo_get_current_mode(connector),
546 NULL);
547 intel_dvo->panel_wants_dither = true;
548 }
549
550 drm_connector_register(connector);
551 return;
552 }
553
554 drm_encoder_cleanup(&intel_encoder->base);
555 kfree(intel_dvo);
556 kfree(intel_connector);
557}
